                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d476">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–1645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Meyer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-16T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 16, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 17—10:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Following are OSS impressions gained from interview with high Japanese
                    Communist recently arrived from Yenan.</p>
                <p>Chinese Communists anti-American at present because our collaboration Chungking,
                    especially enforcing Chungking’s order Japs not surrender Eighth Route Army.
                    This does not extend American people whose support desirable and to be
                    cultivated. Communists confident ability gain control North China soon as
                    American Forces leave. Presence here resented and clashes with small U.S. units
                    may be encouraged to influence American opinion and hasten withdrawal
                    [Marines?].</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Meyer</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
